EEG Visualization

Below is our visualization of the electrode recordings of the EEG data we obtained. The charts are interactive, by holding down the mouse button and selecting an area of the top chart, you can select a range of time for which a cluster of EEG channel data will be shown. Clicking on channels in the legend of the bottom chart will allow you view individual channel activity (click outside of the chart to return to cluster activity). The diagram below both charts is to help visualize the location of the EEG chanels relative to the brain. By dragging the slider, you can view different channels clusters in the bottom chart and their locations will be highlighted on the diagram.

Abel Sandoval
